Fiery Phoenix: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same times costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

Business effect:
If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Players send letter with the hope that MZ will respond and address concerns. Sadly, many mails are ignored for days. Mails must be answered within 24hrs not by autoreply but real custoner service agent.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insults or irritates players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game. Yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Coliseums for different power levels must be returned so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Business Effect:
Players, whether small, medium or big spender, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and update too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts from alliance tiles as players spend on cores and troops to defend it.

A spending boycott is planned to go into effect on Sunday, October 23 at midnight PST.

The initial boycott will last for 2 days (48 hours). We will keep everyone informed of the progress in opening a channel for discussion with MZ. If need be, we may have further boycotting to drive home our stance on our topics.

Please help us spread the word as quickly as possible. Make sure you use farm accounts to spread the word in-game to avoid having your main blocked. FYI, any email with the word "boycott" will bounce on the in-game server.

Please stress the importance of everyone holding out on buying so they take us seriously.

This is a time to return to the simple pleasures of the game. For example: no core wonder fighting, no one gets burned in the radius of the forest that way everyone can keep on playing without spending and constantly resetting wonders. Each kingdom & alliance can choose how they wish to participate in the boycott, in addition to not spending. Be creative, have fun with it.

We will post the letter we're sending here for all to see, and keep everyone updated.

Additionally, many of you have asked which figurehead will be leading the charge & having these discussions with MZ. We've spoke to a few of the top players and they are supporting the boycott. But as for figurehead, we have a legal representative that will speak on our behalf. We will stand together as a unified army against the madness. We have just as much value; our discontent with MZ is no less without a figurehead to act as a mouthpiece. We WILL stand against them! We WILL be heard!

Thank you!

💋💋αηɡεʆα💋💋: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same times costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

Business effect:
If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Players send letter with the hope that MZ will respond and address concerns. Sadly, many mails are ignored for days. Mails must be answered within 24hrs not by autoreply but real custoner service agent.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insults or irritates players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game. Yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Coliseums for different power levels must be returned so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Business Effect:
Players, whether small, medium or big spender, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and update too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts BOYCOTT List

7:42 AM
Lord Kevin: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same times costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

Business effect:
If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Players send letter with the hope that MZ will respond and address concerns. Sadly, many mails are ignored for days. Mails must be answered within 24hrs not by autoreply but real custoner service agent.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insults or irritates players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game. Yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Coliseums for different power levels must be returned so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Business Effect:
Players, whether small, medium or big spender, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and update too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts from alliance tiles as players spend on cores and troops to defend it.

💋💋αηɡεʆα💋💋: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same times costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

Business effect:
If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Players send letter with the hope that MZ will respond and address concerns. Sadly, many mails are ignored for days. Mails must be answered within 24hrs not by autoreply but real custoner service agent.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insults or irritates players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game. Yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Coliseums for different power levels must be returned so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Business Effect:
Players, whether small, medium or big spender, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and update too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts from alliance tiles as players spend on cores and troops to defend it.

💋💋αηɡεʆα💋💋: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same times costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

Business effect:
If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Players send letter with the hope that MZ will respond and address concerns. Sadly, many mails are ignored for days. Mails must be answered within 24hrs not by autoreply but real custoner service agent.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insults or irritates players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game. Yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Coliseums for different power levels must be returned so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Business Effect:
Players, whether small, medium or big spender, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and update too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts from alliance tiles as players spend on cores and troops to defend it.

💋💋αηɡεʆα💋💋: And this list isn't my agenda:
10:04 PM
💋💋αηɡεʆα💋💋: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same times costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

Business effect:
If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Players send letter with the hope that MZ will respond and address concerns. Sadly, many mails are ignored for days. Mails must be answered within 24hrs not by autoreply but real custoner service agent.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insults or irritates players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game. Yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Coliseums for different power levels must be returned so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Business Effect:
Players, whether small, medium or big spender, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and update too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts from alliance tiles as players spend on cores and troops to defend it.

Fiery Phoenix: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as it reinvents the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards must commensurate with or a fraction of the demands of the upgrades.

Major SH releases:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade

September - Cores (Bacchus), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice), garrison, sh24 buildings


Business Effect:
Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. Enough upgrade pacing means longer revenue from that upgrade and longer life span for the game.

>Cost
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players. If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag has improved a bit from last year. But there is still lags, which annoy players, especially during events like SW, coliseum or kvk where lag is worst. Aside from hindering players to play smoothly, it also costs money. Many players won't join events due to lag. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc.

>Glitches

It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE

>Quality of response

d. EVENTS

11:08 AM
Fiery Phoenix: BOYCOTT List
Game of War (GOW)

a. UPGRADES
>Interval of releases
Game upgrades are good as they reinvent the game. However, the recent releases are ridiculously fast making it so hard for everyone to keep up. Many players regardless of size chose to leave the game because they become obsolete after a week of spending and upgrading. There should be at least 3 MONTHS INTERVAL between releases so that players will be able to enjoy and maximize it before the next upgrade. Core updates must be out with at least 1 month interval so players can play with it longer. Fast-paced upgrades choke the players.

Too many game upgrades yet forgetting to upgrade other old game features like dungeons, alliance store, bazaar, secret gifts, quest payouts, etc. to be more relevant and useful for everyone. Payouts or rewards coming these old features must commensurate with or a fraction of the upgrade requirements.

Major SH releases are listed below to show how choking they are:
June (7) - VIP 22, Cores (Nike, Apollo), March 14, Sh23 buildings, Gem preset, Paladin of Sola Gear

July (10) - Sh23 buildings, Battle markings, March 15, Cores (Hephaestus), Gears (Colossus, Oracle), VIP23, 175% March size boosts, Speed up treasury, Hero 61-65

August - Graveyard upgrade, Banners

September - Cores (Bacchus, hera), gear workshop, Sh24 buildings, hidden researches in Academy 24, gear (Exalted Gear)

October - hero 70, Cores (Lady Justice, Perses), garrison, sh24 buildings, gears (Skeleton, supreme marshal)


Players who wanted to play longer but are discouraged due to the upgrades are lost business. They are mostly players spending in the game regardless of amount. If MZ will have enough pacing on the upgrades, players will be happy to pick it up and spend as they feel the need for new challenges in the game. Rather than choke them with weekly upgrades. This also means longer revenue for each upgrade.

>Cost of upgrades
The cost of each upgrade is too much that even big spenders are feeling the burnt in their pockets. This too discourages players thinking, "I just upgraded and spent this much $$$ to max, yet here I am after few days, not maxed. I would need this much again this week to max."

If only upgrades would require just a couple of packs instead of 10s or 100s pack, then players will be more happy. The more players can upgrade, the more active the game will be. The more new players will be interested.

b. SYSTEM/SERVER ISSUES
>Lags
Lag annoys players as it costs them money and also hinders their game. Lag is worst during events like SW, coliseum or kvk and these are the most liked features of the game. Whenever the game is laggy, many players won't play. If this basic element of the game is fixed, more players will be encouraged to join events. Why not eliminate other unnecessary steps/clicks to prevent lags like warrant pop-up, multiple buttons in joining rallies, etc. Also get rid of old and low stats cores, pcs, materials that take up space in the server. Maybe, exchange them for orbs or essences.

>Glitches
Too many glitches in the game that haven't been fixed for months such as tile porting, heroless, skill preset, core not registering, on and off VIP, etc. These glitches are irritating and at the same time costs so much money. It costs so much to upgrade, fir example, to VIP 24 only to have it glitched (on and off) and waste cores.

>App Crash
Game crashes especially during events must be minimal, if not totally eliminated.

If lags and glitches are addressed, more players will join events. The more active the game is, the more revenue for MZ as players will purchase items they need for the event.

c. CUSTOMER SERVICE
>More responsive
Responses to mails must be within 24hrs depending on the gameplay effect of the issue. Categorize concerns based on severity and urgency. Technical issues must be top priorities.

>Quality of response
Complaints on glitches can be validated in your logs. Why not compensate players in full who suffered from the glitches? Compensating us with a fraction of what was lost actually just give a feeling of insult that irate players.

d. EVENTS
>Interval and duration
Kvk is one of the most anticipated and enjoyed parts of the game yet it only happens every 2-3wks. This makes players bored in the game. Making it more frequent like weekly and in longer duration like 24hrs to cover players from different timezones will actually make players happy and more active.

>Coliseum events
Ports for the coliseum event must be earned from infernos and/or bought with gold, loyalty points or copper not just in packs. Open other coliseums for different power levels so that even small players can enjoy the event.

Players, whether small, medium or big spenders, spend in preparation for kvk. Giving more events will encourage them to spend and grow.

e. PACKS
>Content
Current packs are a lot better than last year. However, contents in most packs are outdated already. Items that are in demand and highly needed are often than not absent in packs. Why not remove chests and items that are outdated and replace them with new ones like time orbs, blessing orbs, heroic medals, gems, etc.

>Price
Put ancient advanced teleport in $5-$20 or increase numbers in bigger pack.
Strike a balance on packs. Make it relevant based on needs and do not take out item without replacing them i.e. packs for maxed account.

f. MONSTERS AND TILES
>Drops
Make drops from monsters relevant and updated too. Gems, pcs, cores or materials that are new and in demand.

OTHER SUGGESTIONS:
>Alliance City-Bazaar
The alliance city is a nice adornment in the game but it should be made useful. The bazaar in particular should enable players to trade items between themselves. Copper should be varying or increasing. Items that can be sold and bought must be replaced/updated 2x or once a month. It should also sell relevant items like heroic medals, orbs, 45min hemlock, instant execution, etc.

-There should be feature like 1) one button to use all hero xp and VIP pts. And the likes; 2) combine lower march size boosts, rss boosts and other boosts.

-Make home ports useful by enabling players to choose a new home kingdom if it is staying for more than a month in a new kingdom.

-Alliance tile
Bring back the good gifts from alliance tiles as players spend on cores and troops to defend it.

This message is regarding the application Game of War: Fire Age (GOW).

We are currently situated in kingdoms with the Protected status, 767-849 to be exact. The last kingdom to become Ancient was approximately 2 months ago. The kingdoms 767-849 are in that range to go ancient (looking at previous kingdoms to go ancient).

In fairness to players who populate the kingdoms in question we would like to be treated as all other players in this game environment. We feel our spending on this application has become fruitless at this point and the advancement of our status to Ancient Kingdoms would boost activity and enhance the enjoyment of the game therefore promote greater spending for the offered in app purchases.

All contact with them has become untenable. We have come to yourselves in hope of you understanding our predicament for what MZ is currently doing to us and that you can please do what is needed to ensure we are treated fairly like other kingdoms and players in GOW.

We apologise for the mass amount of identical mails regarding this, however we are at a loose end with this situation that we find ourselves in, we hope you understand.

Thank you for your time.
